  "plan": {
    "id": "usd_swaption_normal_vol",
    "description": "USD swaption normal-vol surface calibrated against a 3\u00d73 (expiry \u00d7 tenor) grid of SwaptionVol quotes, chained on a USD-OIS discount curve and USD-SOFR-3M forward curve that are bootstrapped in the same plan. Step 1 produces the USD-OIS discount curve from deposit and IRS quotes; step 2 bootstraps the USD-SOFR-3M forward curve from FRA quotes; step 3 fits per-bucket SABR (\u03b2=0) parameters to normal vols quoted in basis points. The envelope is fully self-bootstrapping from quotes \u2014 no hand-entered curves in initial_market. The produced VolCube is keyed as 'USD-SWAPTION-NORMAL-VOL' and is retrievable via MarketContext::get_vol_provider(). Note: swaption_vol calibration produces a VolCube (not a VolSurface), so the accessor is get_vol_provider rather than get_surface. The grid uses 3 expiries (1y, 2y, 5y from base 2026-05-08) \u00d7 3 swap tenors (2y, 5y, 10y) \u00d7 3 strikes (ATM-50bp, ATM, ATM+50bp) for a total of 27 quotes. Normal vols range from 55\u201380 bp, representative of a 5% rate environment.",
